            </p>
         </div>
         
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
            <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><g type="crux"/> <w lemma="νικάω">Νηκᾷ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="τύχη">τύχη</w>
                    <lb n="2"/><w lemma="Πράσινος">Πραϲίνων</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶν</w> <w lemma="ὀρθόδοξος">ὀρ 
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/>θοδόξων</w> <g type="crux"/> <space extent="unknown"/>
                </ab>
         </div>
         
         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>
               The fortune of the orthodox Greens triumphs!
            </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For the epithet Orthodox apparently used of the Greens see also Text 15; Grégoire also restored a reference to the Greens as orthodox in another text at Ephesos, <title>I.Eph.</title> 1192.2, 
            but that is far from certain.</p>
